[01:42.20]	For this is from the present--how you take
[01:45.48]	The offers we have sent you.
[01:47.80]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	There's the point.
[01:49.43]MARK ANTONY	Which do not be entreated to, but weigh
[01:52.50]	What it is worth embraced.
[01:54.68]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	And what may follow,
[01:56.46]	To try a larger fortune.
[01:58.50]POMPEY	You have made me offer
[02:00.48]	Of Sicily, Sardinia; and I must
[02:02.93]	Rid all the sea of pirates; then, to send
[02:06.07]	Measures of wheat to Rome; this 'greed upon
[02:09.34]	To part with unhack'd edges, and bear back
[02:12.62]	Our targes undinted.
[02:14.39]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	|
[02:14.80]	|
[02:15.21]MARK ANTONY	| That's our offer.
[02:16.77]	|
[02:17.18]LEPIDUS	|
[02:17.59]POMPEY	Know, then,
[02:18.68]	I came before you here a man prepared
[02:21.68]	To take this offer: but Mark Antony
[02:24.48]	Put me to some impatience: though I lose
[02:27.62]	The praise of it by telling, you must know,
[02:30.89]	When Caesar and your brother were at blows,
[02:34.23]	Your mother came to Sicily and did find
[02:37.37]	Her welcome friendly.
