[04:02.87]POMPEY	I know thee now: how farest thou, soldier?
[04:06.01]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Well;
[04:06.76]	And well am like to do; for, I perceive,
[04:09.76]	Four feasts are toward.
[04:11.74]POMPEY	Let me shake thy hand;
[04:13.64]	I never hated thee: I have seen thee fight,
[04:16.92]	When I have envied thy behavior.
[04:19.51]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Sir,
[04:20.19]	I never loved you much; but I ha' praised ye,
[04:23.53]	When you have well deserved ten times as much
[04:27.08]	As I have said you did.
[04:29.05]POMPEY	Enjoy thy plainness,
[04:30.83]	It nothing ill becomes thee.
[04:33.15]	Aboard my galley I invite you all:
[04:35.87]	Will you lead, lords?
[04:37.65]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	|
[04:38.06]	|
[04:38.46]MARK ANTONY	| Show us the way, sir.
[04:40.24]	|
[04:40.65]LEPIDUS	|
